Components and literals derived from ECC
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Copied verbatim (with a per-file attribution comment at the copy site):

  * Secret / approval-command / sensitive-path detection literals
    (SECRET_PATTERNS, APPROVAL_COMMANDS, SENSITIVE_PATHS) — from
    scripts/hooks/governance-capture.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/redaction/patterns.py.

  * Model cost RATE_TABLE (per-1M-token rates) — from
    scripts/hooks/cost-tracker.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/cost/rates.py.

Re-expressed in Python (pattern reuse; same logic, idiomatic rewrite):

  * Data-home resolution (MANTHANA_DATA_HOME) — from
    scripts/lib/agent-data-home.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/datahome.py.

  * Collector / adapter-registry pattern — from
    scripts/lib/session-adapters/{registry,canonical-session,claude-history}.js
    into collectors/src/manthana/collectors/base.py.

  * JSONL line-handling edge cases (skip unparseable lines, string-or-array
    content, nested blocks) — from scripts/hooks/session-end.js
    (extractSessionSummary) into
    collectors/src/manthana/collectors/claude_code.py.

  * State-store layer (schema-validated JSON documents, query API) and the
    versioned migration framework — from scripts/lib/state-store/{index,
    queries,migrations,schema}.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/store/{store,migrations,tables}.py.

  * SQLite connection pragmas (foreign_keys=ON, WAL) — from
    scripts/lib/state-store/index.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/store/engine.py.

  * Cost token-summation logic — from scripts/hooks/cost-tracker.js
    (sumUsageFromTranscript) into agent/src/manthana/agent/cost/cost.py.

State-store entity definitions in schemas/state-store.schema.json were the
starting point that Manthana's schema package (schemas/src/manthana/schemas/)
extends with the Turn / Session / Compaction entities.
